50|$|The <b>African</b> Women's <b>Development</b> <b>Fund</b> (AWDF) is {{the first}} pan-African {{foundation}} to support the work of women's rights organisations in Africa. AWDF was founded in 2001 by Bisi Adeleye-Fayemi, Joana Foster and Hilda M. Tardia. AWDF belongs to the International Network of Women’s Funds, an umbrella organisation for feminist foundations that focus on supporting women's human rights.|$|R
